广元市民扎堆摘口罩喝茶，多名公职人员被追责。
Guang Yuan citizens gather masks to drink tea, a number of public officials were held accountable.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
澎湃新闻记者 钟煜豪近日，四川广元因“市民扎堆摘口罩喝坝坝茶”颇受关注，2月23日最新消息显示，涉及该问题的广元市城管执法局广场服务中心主任张东等人被党纪立案审查、政务立案调查。
People in Guangyuan, Sichuan Province, were caught up in a recent news report that Zhang Dong, director of the Plaza of Guangzhou Municipal Administration of Law Enforcement (CCLEB), was investigated and investigated by the Communist Party.
据中新网报道，此前2月20日，广元市发布应对新型冠状病毒肺炎疫情应急指挥部第18号公告，公告第四点提出，市指挥部第2号公告中要求暂停营业的茶楼、洗浴保健、体育健身、美容保健、游乐场所等5类商业业态中，恢复室外坝坝茶、室外体育、室外游乐场所营业，美甲店允许开业，其他商业业态经营网点已暂停营业的应立即恢复营业。
Earlier on Feb. 20, Guangyuan City issued a notice No. 18 in response to the new coronavirus pneumonia emergency command, the announcement made in point 4, the city headquarters No.2 called for the suspension of business tea houses, bathing health care, physical fitness, beauty health care, amusement park business, re-open outdoor dam tea, outdoor sports, outdoor playground, allowed to open, other business operations immediately resumed business.
不过，上述公告发布的次日，随着部分商业业态的恢复，很多地方特别是城区出现了大量人员聚集的情况。
However, the day after the announcement, there was a large concentration of people in many places, especially in urban areas, as part of the business sector resumed.
其中，广元利州广场的坝坝茶吸引大量人员聚集、生意火爆。
Among them, the dam tea of Guangyuan Lizhou square attracts a large number of people to gather, business is booming.
随后，一条展现广元市民扎堆卸口罩喝坝坝茶的视频引起全国网友关注。
Afterwards, a video showing Guang Yuan citizens stacking masks and drinking dam tea attracted the attention of netizens across the country.
视频截图2月21日19时，广元市应对新型冠状病毒肺炎疫情应急指挥部发布公告称：随着部分商业业态的恢复，很多地方特别是城区出现了大量人员聚集的情况。
Video screener Feb. 21, 19: 00, Guangyuan City to respond to the new coronavirus pneumonia emergency command issued a notice: With the resumption of some commercial situation, many places, particularly in urban areas, a large number of people have gathered.
市应急指挥部提醒广大群众，当前仍处于重大突发公共卫生事件Ⅰ级应急响应期间，疫情传播风险较大，要自觉远离人员聚集场所，不参与人员聚集活动，在人员较多场所要佩戴口罩。
The Municipal Emergency Command reminded the general public that the epidemic is still in a major public health emergency stage I emergency response period, that the risk of spreading the epidemic is high, that people should be kept away from places where people congregate, that people should not participate in gatherings, and that masks should be worn in places with large numbers of personnel.
各室外经营商户要拉大经营摊位间距，每个摊位外围边缘保持1.5米以上距离，并做好经营场地消杀工作。
Outdoor operators should increase the spacing between their stands, keep a distance of more than 1.5 meters at the outer edge of each booth, and do a good job of eliminating and eliminating the operation site.
城管执法、市场监管部门和基层社区要加强监督、管理，严重违反规定的，依法予以处罚。
Urban administration law enforcement, market supervision departments and grass-roots communities shall strengthen supervision and management, and those who seriously violate regulations shall be punished according to law.
2月22日22时，广元市应对新型冠状病毒肺炎疫情应急指挥部再发公告：鉴于当前新冠肺炎疫情防控的严峻形势，为有效防范人员聚集可能带来的新冠肺炎病毒传播风险，现就有关事项公告如下。
At 2200 hours on February 22, the Guangyuan Municipal Emergency Command issued another notice on the new coronavirus pneumonia: In view of the severe situation of prevention and control of the new coronavirus, we hereby announce the following in order to effectively prevent the risk of transmission of the new coronavirus.
暂停室外体育中的足球、篮球、排球活动，禁止举行广场舞、柔力球等群体性文体活动，禁止在经营场所、公共场所打麻将、纸牌等娱乐活动；企事业单位不得举行各类非生产性的聚集性活动。
Football, basketball and volleyball activities in outdoor sports shall be suspended, mass cultural and sports activities such as square dancing and flexible ball shall be prohibited, and recreational activities such as playing Mahjong and playing cards in public places shall be prohibited. Enterprises and institutions shall not hold all kinds of non-productive and collective activities.
澎湃新闻注意到，2月22日，广元市委副书记、市长邹自景在市城区调研餐饮业、露天商业业态恢复情况时强调，当前仍处于重大突发公共卫生事件Ⅰ级应急响应期间，疫情传播风险较大，各级各部门要继续保持高度警惕，严防人员聚集。
Peng Pai News noted that on February 22, Mayor Zou Ziging, deputy secretary of Guangyuan Municipal Committee, studied the recovery of catering industry and open air commerce in urban areas.
他指出，允许餐馆提供堂食，但要严格采取隔桌就餐等方式，保持安全距离，严格控制顾客流量，坚决避免人员聚集。
Restaurants are allowed to serve parlours, he said, but tables should be used strictly to keep a safe distance from customers, strictly control the flow of customers and resolutely avoid gathering people.
要加强就餐场所通风，暂停使用中央空调系统，科学规范做好内部消杀消毒工作，保持顾客就餐场所安全卫生整洁。
We will strengthen ventilation in dining areas, suspend the use of central air-conditioning systems, scientifically standardize the internal disinfection work, and keep customers eating places safe and clean.
报道还称，室外坝坝茶和室外游乐场所恢复营业后，邹自景非常关心如何有效降低疫情传播风险，切实保障人民群众的健康安全。
Zou Ziging is very concerned about how to effectively reduce the risk of spreading the disease and ensure people's health and safety.
他来到水上公园、嘉陵广场、千佛崖景区、凤凰山公园等地，实地察看室外坝坝茶经营点的摊位设置和疫情防控措施落实情况。
He came to the water park, Jialing Square, Qianfeiya Scenic Area, Phoenix Hill Park, and other places, to see the outdoor dam tea business site booths set-up and epidemic prevention and control measures.
邹自景要求，室外商业业态相关经营商户要严格执行市应急指挥部的要求，扩大经营摊位间距，防止人员聚集。
Zou Zi-jing requested that the outdoor business state of business-related operators strictly implement the requirements of the City Emergency Command, expand the distance between operating stalls to prevent the accumulation of personnel.
要加强消费环境和茶具饮具的清洗消毒，确保消费者饮食安全。
Must strengthen the consumption environment and the tea utensils cleaning disinfection, guarantees the consumer food safety.
要加强对市民的劝导，严禁在坝坝茶摊位打麻将、纸牌。
To strengthen public persuasion, it is strictly forbidden to play mahjong and solitaire at the dam tea stand.
城管执法、市场监管部门和基层组织要加强监督管理，确保不发生人员聚集。
City law enforcement, market supervision and grass-roots organizations should strengthen supervision and management to ensure that no people congregate.
据四川在线2月23日消息，广元6例确诊的新冠肺炎患者全部治愈出院，连续20天无新增新冠肺炎确诊病例，现有疑似病例0例，正接受医学观察10人。
A total of 6 cases of newly diagnosed pneumonia in Guangyuan were cured and discharged. There were no new confirmed cases of pneumonia for 20 days.
